{"id":"2205.09886","submitter":"Miguel Aguilera","authors":"Miguel Aguilera, Masanao Igarashi, Hideaki Shimazaki","title":"Nonequilibrium thermodynamics of the asymmetric Sherrington-Kirkpatrick\n  model","comments":null,"journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"cond-mat.stat-mech cond-mat.dis-nn","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  Most systems in nature operate far from equilibrium, exhibiting\ntime-asymmetric, irreversible dynamics, giving rise to a positive entropy\nproduction as they exchange energy and matter with their environment. We study\nthe stochastic thermodynamics of the asymmetric Sherrington-Kirkpatrick system\nwith synchronous and asynchronous updates as a prototypical model of\nlarge-scale nonequilibrium processes. We employ a path integral method to\ncalculate a generating functional over trajectories and derive exact solutions\nof the order parameters, path entropy, and steady-state entropy production of\ninfinitely large networks. Entropy production peaks at a critical\norder-disorder phase transition, but is more prominent in a regime with\nquasi-deterministic disordered dynamics. Large entropy production can thus\nlinked with radically different scenarios, and multiple thermodynamic\nquantities are necessary to explain the system. These results contribute to an\nexact analytical theory for studying the thermodynamics of large-scale\nnonequilibrium systems and their phase transitions.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 19 May 2022 22:28:03 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 14 Jul 2022 10:26:05 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Wed, 1 Feb 2023 13:58:48 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-02-02"}
