atient has hypertensive pressures in the brain as well as\nreduced flow to the gut. Wave-intensity analysis suggests that the HLHS patient\nhas irregular circulatory function during light upright exercise conditions and\nthat predicted wall-shear stresses are lower than normal, suggesting the HLHS\npatient may have hypertension.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 20 May 2022 14:31:05 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-05-23"}
